\par }{COMBAT
\par }{\fs20 Being bullied by bigger, stronger creatures has taught goblins to exploit what few advantages they have: sheer numbers and malicious ingenuity. The concept of a fair fight is mean
ingless in their society. They favor ambushes, overwhelming odds, dirty tricks, and any other edge they can devise. 
\par Goblins have a poor grasp of strategy and are cowardly by nature, tending to flee the field if a battle turns against them. With proper sup
ervision, though, they can implement reasonably complex plans, and in such circumstances their numbers can be a deadly advantage.
